==Abstract==

This IIP specifies lexicographic ordering of transaction inputs and outputs to improve privacy and reduce fingerprinting. It implements BIP 69 for INTcoin.

==Motivation==

Transaction input and output ordering can leak information:
* Change output position may reveal which output is change
* Input ordering may indicate wallet software
* Deterministic ordering improves privacy by standardization

==Specification==

===Input Ordering===

Inputs are sorted lexicographically by:
# Previous txid (32 bytes, little-endian)
# Previous output index (4 bytes, little-endian)

<pre>
sort_key(input) = (input.prevout.hash, input.prevout.n)
</pre>

===Output Ordering===

Outputs are sorted lexicographically by:
# Amount (8 bytes, little-endian)
# ScriptPubKey (variable length)

<pre>
sort_key(output) = (output.nValue, output.scriptPubKey)
</pre>

===Algorithm===

<pre>
def sort_transaction(tx):
    tx.vin.sort(key=lambda x: (x.prevout.hash, x.prevout.n))
    tx.vout.sort(key=lambda x: (x.nValue, x.scriptPubKey))
</pre>

===Exceptions===

Deterministic ordering MAY be skipped when:
* Using SIGHASH_SINGLE (output position matters)
* Protocol requires specific ordering
* User explicitly requests alternative ordering

==Rationale==

===Why Lexicographic?===

* Deterministic: Same inputs always produce same order
* Simple to implement
* No information leakage from ordering

===Privacy Benefit===

When all wallets use the same ordering:
* Change outputs cannot be identified by position
* Wallet software cannot be fingerprinted by ordering

